Subject:Re: [child_lit] Blind protagonists
Emily Gregory, a 12 year old pianist, in Madeleine L'Engle's The Young
Unicorn isn't the protagonist, but she features prominently in the story.

-Amy

On Thu, Oct 25, 2012 at 4:36 PM, Virginia Lowe <vlowe888@tpg.com.au> wrote:

> Susan in Lucy Boston's "Chimneys of Green Knowe" is blind. Her father,
> against the wishes of her mother, brings her a companion, a negro boy from
> the Caribbean I think he was - Jacob - and he teaches her to climb  trees
> and do many many things. It's a marvellous portrayal of both how girls were
> treated, how the blind were mollycoddled and the courage of Jacob and Susan
> to defy all the restrictions against them. As well as being an exciting
> adventure story. And brilliantly written.
>
